rComments: This prof teaches one of the most meaningless classes at Telfer, but he is one of the most high-quality profs. He makes the class extremely intriguing and real-life-focused by inviting guest speakers and using trending news. You can get 20% by just writing reflections and discussion forums. Cases and final exams are tough since A+ is "scarcity".

Brought on some very engaging speakers, I networked with one. Enjoyed his class a lot, made me like ethics even more, especially since it's considered a boring (but important) topic in CFA. Can also have banter about sports

Course itself: You buy a case pack for analysis, lots of group work, some individual participation/assessments, then a Final

This prof is such a legend that he plays The Wolf of Wall Street in the class to teach us about finance ethics. He tries to keep the class interesting by incorporating movies, trending news and discussions. If it weren't for my âne team members, getting an A would be totally viable. Only thing I hate is how group work occupies over 50% of grades.

Great guy! I highly recommend taking him for ADM4355! Although some of the content can be boring, he tries to make it as interesting as possible. He also wants you to succeed and genuinely seems to care.

Professor Safi is a great professor. Very polite and engaging and I'm glad I took his class . If you do the work, attend the lectures and participate in the discussions on brightspace, it's an easy A.

He is boring at times but also very nice and the class is organized/straightforward. The cases aren't the easiest but he basically gives you 20% free (participation+easy assignments). Absolutely no need for the textbook, just read the slides and do the practice questions and you'll be fine. Workload is normal for a capstone course.

Nice prof who seems smart enough to actually know how to teach stuff, but this course is extremely time-consuming and your can basically drop your course if your team consists of tossers. Despite being good at teaching, the prof feels like professor Archibald 2.0, which means that he can be bureaucratic and hard to reach sometimes. Dont expect A+.

Professor Safi was excellent. For an online class with content that could be presented in a way that most would consider rather bland, he really brought life to it and sought to engage his students. You will have to work for it, but he will make you informed that it won't be a challenge should you apply yourself. Perhaps my favourite UO prof.

This course has an insane workload that will occupy 60% of your time, so I suggest that you put it in a light semester. The prof is the King of this course since he is the only one teaching, which leaves you no choice to go with him. Find a competent group and get it over with as soon as possible. Don't expect to receive high grades for this class.
You got to work hard to do well. To do well, you also need good team members
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Lots of homework', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Would recommend this course, very insightful. The CSL grades can be VERY disheartening in the beginning, but if you keep implementing the feedback you will see a payoff in the end.

Top 5 Profs in my books at Telfer. Cracks jokes, super engaging and really tries to interact with the class. Was shocked that he would remember everyone's name and specific things we said. Always approachable and willing to take the time to chat. Great videos & guest lectures. Tough exam, but lots of bonus marks to be earned during the semester.

I really enjoyed this class, didn't know what to expect at the beginning but ended up being one of my favourite classes. The CSL assignments were actual consulting projects for socially responsible companies. Really engaging classes focused on strategy theory and practice, cases and discussions. Heavy summative, but no tests or exams!

Good prof although he can seem a little awkward sometimes in the front of the class. Often tries too hard to force students to participate. Listening at his lectures had very little value to your final grade as the grades were all based on assignments, projects and presentations. It seems like he cares & puts more effort than other profs at Telfer

Best lecturer of my first year. Encourages participation and discussion, and he is always smiling. Assignments are a good way to boost your grade. Exams are heavy but he makes it clear what will be on it so you can prepare and is a fair grader.

He's a nice and approachable guy who manages to make the most boring subject somewhat interesting. Although the midterm was difficult, he gave bonus marks to everyone to help them raise their marks. The final exam was extremely easy. The mini-assignments are basically free marks if you bother doing them. The group project is also quite simple.

Great teacher! I had 3 hour lectures with him and he made them interesting and engaging! Pay attention to the slides mostly, the textbook isn't as important. Mid terms and the final weren't tough and he makes sure you know what to expect for them. Also he's a fair grader.  He is one of my favourite profs so far.
Really good prof. He actually makes 3 hour lectures interesting. Really tries to engage the class

Young, attractive, relatable, funny - all helps pass the course with an Easy A. Just know your slides. Was kind of annoying he wouldn't post the slides before the lecture so you couldn't prepare. Didn't use the textbook a lot. Super easy midterms and final.

Didn't attend more then half the lectures and got a good grade still. Buy the textbook do your notes/readings, or just the slides. Do the weekly mini assignments for easy marks. Downfalls include: Expect to need to know random little charts in the slides/readings. Also watch the videos shown in class may come up on a midterm or final exam.

He cares for his students and tries to be interactive but the lectures are pretty much useless. Not necessary to show up to pass the course. I don't think his lectures actually prepare students for passing the exam.

Pouya was literally the best prof ever. He cared a lot about his students and that really showed during his lectures. His expectations were very clear and the exam and midterm was all content discussed in class. Showing up to lectures really helps prepare for the final. Memorize his lecture slides and you'll be good for exam.
he tries so hard to make the lectures interactive. pouya is a great professor, mind you he posts the slides so i would suggest going over them after and pick out what is important

Very interactive class, always wanted to hear the opinions and thoughts of as many students as possible. Also made the instructions and guidelines very clear for tests/projects in order to score an A. Fair midterm and final. Definitely recommend this prof.
Very humorous, love to get the class engaged and up and moving.  A lot of videos, be careful they will be on exams, as well as an overall great professor.  Would have him as a prof again.
Great prof, very engaging lectures and does a great job of making the class interesting.

Pouya has very engaging lecturers to where you feel as though you are actually learning without being board.  Very clear expectations and gives marks each week for about 10 minutes of work which is very handy.  Midterm was very fair and even gave a bonus 4% for admitting one of the questions was worded awkwardly.  Highly recommend.

Excellent prof and fair grader. Transparent about workload and course expectations. Course partly based on CFA material, as described in course outline. Overall, passionate and engaging . Highly recommend this class. Participation a key component, as it is a discussion based class. You get half your marks just for showing up. No midterm, only final

Tough prof. and Tough grader Have to speak out every class, otherwise you will lose your participation mark. Very heavy reading for this class.  All the final exam multiple choices questions are from CFA. The volume of questions in the final exam is huge.

Great lectures, highly motivated to teach and really tries to get students to interact and participate. I would definitely recommend you take this class with him. Accessible out of class even if it's just to chat or get clarity on the topics. Fair grader and fair exams if you attend class. My favourite class so far!
Extremely interactive lectures
Great prof! Participation in lectures makes it more enjoyable
Total lad. Great teacher, lectures are interesting and participation heavy. Cares about his students.
involves the class to discuss and is very intresting
